<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>I am running i3wm with thunar. I am running brave as browser. Whenever i try to edit the file name this happens suddenly jumps to search files. Here check this video <a href="https://imgur.com/a/8sjEfkV">https://imgur.com/a/8sjEfkV</a> But when i am logged into xfce session it works ok. How to fix this. The details i got from running xprop is here</p> <p><code> _GTK_THEME_VARIANT(UTF8_STRING) = _NET_WM_DESKTOP(CARDINAL) = 0 WM_STATE(WM_STATE): window state: Normal icon window: 0x0 _NET_WM_STATE(ATOM) = _NET_WM_STATE_MODAL WM_HINTS(WM_HINTS): Client accepts input or input focus: True Initial state is Normal State. window id # of group leader: 0x4a00002 WM_TRANSIENT_FOR(WINDOW): window id # 0x3a0000f _NET_WM_OPAQUE_REGION(CARDINAL) = 0, 0, 619, 1014 _MOTIF_WM_HINTS(_MOTIF_WM_HINTS) = 0x3, 0x1, 0x1, 0x0, 0x0 XdndAware(ATOM) = BITMAP _NET_WM_SYNC_REQUEST_COUNTER(CARDINAL) = 77595246, 77595247 _NET_WM_USER_TIME(CARDINAL) = 3792371 _NET_WM_USER_TIME_WINDOW(WINDOW): window id # 0x4a0026d WM_CLIENT_LEADER(WINDOW): window id # 0x4a00002 _NET_WM_PID(CARDINAL) = 472587 WM_LOCALE_NAME(STRING) = &quot;en_US.UTF-8&quot; WM_CLIENT_MACHINE(STRING) = &quot;FG204&quot; WM_NORMAL_HINTS(WM_SIZE_HINTS): program specified minimum size: 432 by 419 WM_PROTOCOLS(ATOM): protocols WM_DELETE_WINDOW, WM_TAKE_FOCUS, _NET_WM_PING, _NET_WM_SYNC_REQUEST WM_CLASS(STRING) = &quot;xdg-desktop-portal-gnome&quot;, &quot;xdg-desktop-portal-gnome&quot; _NET_WM_WINDOW_TYPE(ATOM) = _NET_WM_WINDOW_TYPE_DIALOG WM_ICON_NAME(STRING) = &quot;All Files&quot; _NET_WM_ICON_NAME(UTF8_STRING) = &quot;All Files&quot; WM_NAME(STRING) = &quot;All Files&quot; _NET_WM_NAME(UTF8_STRING) = &quot;All Files&quot; </code></p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Soham-Chatterjee"> /u/Soham-Chatterjee </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/vygqpw/in_brave_when_download_a_file_whenever_i_try_to/">[link]</a></span> &#32;